# 9.1 General

Coordination is the exchange of information and control responsibility between ATC units.

Controllers shall ensure:
- Timely transfer of communication
- Accurate transfer of control
- Clear understanding of traffic situation

---

## Types of Coordination

- Verbal (voice)
- System-based (handoff)
- Pre-agreed procedures

---

## Responsibility

The transferring controller remains responsible until:
- The receiving controller accepts the aircraft, or
- Communication transfer is completed
